ost_step.2: Multiply the weekly earnings by the number of weeks in a harvest season (223).
ost_step.3: To find out the total earnings over 73 harvest seasons, multiply the annual earnings by 73.

Firstly, we need to figure out how much Lewis earns annually. We can do this by multiplying his weekly earnings by the number of weeks in a single harvest season.

He earns $1357 per week. 

So, in one harvest season (which lasts 223 weeks), he'd earn:
\[ \text{Annual Earnings} = 1357 \times 223 \]

Now let’s calculate this product:
\[ 1357 \times 223 = 303711 \]

\[ \text{Total Earnings Over 73 Harvest Seasons} = \text{Annual Earnings} \times 73 \]
\[ \text{Total Earnings Over 73 Harvest Seasons} = 303711 \times 73 \]

Calculating this will give us the grand total of how much he'll earn over those years
